commitResults.messageBody: Update developer guide to include relevant user stories

IdUtil enables generation of unique IDs for
doctor, patient, and appointments

Create new appointment class which encapsulates
a doctor and a patient
Create internal feature to get person by nric
Update test cases for new methods added

Create a number of changes to support adding
of appointments to MediCLI

 A typical patient management system would want
to track the appointments that the patients have.

The appointment class establishes an appointment
in a very basic sense which is between a doctor and
a patient at a particular date.

This allows for the very basic tracking of appointments.

Add UI to manage appointments

MediCLI needs to be able to display appointments
as they are added. Presently there is no way to do so.

This commit adds a UI that displays appointments  in a
list beside the person cards. This allows the user to see
all appointments and persons in one go, making it
convenient.
